name: Industrial Modern Lamp
description: Task light. Simple. Utilitarian. Industrial. We've taken a vintage 1950s lamp by The Northern Electric Company and given it a couple of stylized, yet subtle upgrades: • all new wiring, • vintage inspired plug with cloth-covered cord (black) • nickel-plated socket and turn knob • 60 Watt Edison-style bulb Made in the USA

name: 1920's Vintage Medical Stand
description: End table. Circa 1920's/1930's vintage medical operating room stand with stainless steel tray. The cast iron base contains two swivel casters for cruising your drinks from the kitchen to the dining room. Original t-shaped adjustable handle for taking the tray up to crazy heights. The stainless steel tray is removable. Heavy patina and some surface rust. The tray is ever so slightly bent to the right if you are looking at it- please see picture numero 1. We thought about having this bent back, but we decided that it added just a little bit more character, so we left it. Great for a side table for drinks, reading lamp, or laptop workstation. Adjustable tray height: 33" to 52"

name: Vintage Game Board
description: Five hundred. Old school, skee ball/bowling hybrid game board that can live on your counter, console stereo system, or on your wall. You could probably still play this if you wanted to, but we recommend just sitting back and looking at it. Paint is fading, but still has some great color. Hanging wire has been added to the back for easy wall mounting.

name: Industrial Timer
description: Time's up. Industrial photographic timer. Great mid century piece that works with precision. There's no buzzer on this unit, but you could still use it around the game table, in the kitchen, or in the office. Made by the Industrial Timer Corporation in the USA. Dimensions: 5"Wx5"Hx3"D

name: Art Deco Jars
description: Preserve details. Collection of three art deco glass jars with metal screw lids. Each jar has unique deco design, shape, and size. Perfect for your collection of widgets or for fresh flowers on the picnic table.

name: Vintage Green Basket
description: One potato...Vintage green potato basket. Metal with rubber coating for durability and long life. Black handle, excellent design. Perfect for stashing books next to the bed or your favorite throw next to the sofa. Or just practice your long shot from across the office... Dimensions: 15"Wx14"T

name: Frank Lloyd Wright Book Triolgy
description: Innovative text. This rare trilogy contains three mid century classics in wonderful condition. All three books are tight, bright, clean, sharp-cornered, and surprisingly well-preserved. The dust jackets continue to serve their purpose well, but do have some minor tears and slight wear on the spines, edges, and corners. The box is flaking in a few spots, but the FLW logo is still bold and bright. These books are wonderfully illustrated with architectural drawings, photographs, portraits, and rich text. Boxed set contains the following books: "The Future of Architecture" 1953 "The Natural House" 1954 "The Living City" 1958 The first book, "The Living City", contains a magnificent 8-page square full color fold out of Wright's Broadacre City- the distillation of a quarter century's work. You can view more images of this item on our blog

name: Vintage Mine Respirator
description: Industrial safety. Breathe easy with this vintage mining respirator. The graphics and design of the tin box are worth the price of admission alone. Comes with respirator in gorgeous metallic blue, box of dust filters, instruction booklet, box, and extra filter. Awesome condition. Tin box has some slight rust and patina.

name: Danish Stainless Steel Tray
description: Modern service. Mid century modern Danish serving tray. Perfect for your cheddars. Three partitions to keep garnishes in perfect isolation. Marked "Kalmar" 18/8 Stainless Steel. Made in Denmark. Some light surface scratches. Dimensions: 14.5"Lx11"Wx1"D

name: Vintage Branding Iron
description: Hot property. Antique cattle branding iron from an unknown ranch. Brand is composed of a "Y" and an arrow. Nice design. Use it as a fire poker or just set it next to your fireplace. Dimensions: 36.5"Hx4.5"Wx2"D

name: Nautical Metal Storage
description: Gorgeous graphics. Metal storage box for boat decal letters-marked 1958. The lid features the "ABC's" of the original contents and the front sports some fancy advertising and two speedy speed boats. The paint is peeling in all the right ways and the colors are fantastic. The inside features three metal slotted compartments for storing all your favorite goods. Does NOT contain original decal letters... Dimensions: 15"Lx12"Wx9"D Made in the USA

name: Vintage Camera Collection #1
description: Click click. Become an instant collector! Aluminum, hand-stamped leather cases, and true US and German craftsmanship come together to make this a truly unique and beautiful collection of vintage photographic tools. All cameras are in great condition and seem to function properly, but have not been tested because film is not readily available for most of these models. Cameras date between 1946 and 1962- group them together or display individually as art pieces. Here’s what you get:   • Brownie Target Six-20- 1947ish  • Argus Argoflex Seventy-five (stamped leather case)- early 50s   • Photrix Quick-B- early 50's • Kodak Brownie Bull’s Eye With Kodalite Midget Flash- 1955  • Argus C3- late 50's (shoe-mount meter, bulb flash, and leather case)

name: Atlas Jars (pair)
description: Strong glass. Two Atlas jars for displaying your wizzers, bizzers, gidgets, and widgets. Or perfect for that spring time bouquet. Lockable glass lids and bold Atlas logo. Heavy glass with green tint. Metal locking mechanism to keep that glass lid from running off. Some nice surface rust on metal lock.

name: Industrial Art Litho #3- Original(1892)
description: Symmetry and design. Original industrial art litho print from 1892- "Types of Screws". Original print by Sackett and Wilhelms Litho Co New York. Amazing detail and history of the screw. Great industrial design art piece with symmetry, composition, and form. Professionally matted on acid-free archival matt board with foam core backing. Excellent condition- very few marks. No rips or tears within matted area. Print Dimensions: 16"Wx20"T Matt Dimensions: 22"Wx28"T

name: Tartan Ice Chest
description: Portable fridge This is one of the most unique coolers we have ever found. All metal design- Yellow and black plaid clashes oh so perfectly with the snake skin detailed lid. All metal construction with an industrial handle. Removable metal container has two wonderful illustrations (winter cottage and summer beach) and usage examples. Tartan logo features a pipe-playin' Scotsman and great mid century font. BEER NOT INCLUDED! Sorry. Dimensions: 16"Lx9"Wx11"D

name: Shaving Mirror
description: Trim mustache. Shave your beard, fix your lipstick, reflect life. This nickel-plated Apollo mirror has a cast iron base so it can also be used to keep your desk in order with the window down. Wear appropriate for age- great patina and character. Works in just about every room of the house. Stands about 10.5" tall.

name: Mid Century Globe
description: Topo world. Mid Century 12" Replogle globe with topographic features. Great details and beautiful colors- fantastic condition.

name: Vintage Book Collection- Explore
description: World traveler. Another great collection of vintage books to make your shelf sing with personality. The color palette flows from one text to the next and each volume has a unique and personal texture and graphic style. • "Journey Into A Strange Land" Copyright, 1956 • "Wildlife of the Pacific Northwest", 1954 • "It happened In Taos" Copyright, 1946 • "The Illustrated Book of Wild Animals of the World" Copyright, 1948

name: Black Tool Box
description: Carry all. Distressed black tool box with perfectly placed dents, paint drips, scratches, and patina. Riveted metal handle, metal latch, and loads of character. Dimensions: 16Lx7.5Wx7.5D

name: First Aid Kit
description: Heal it. Johnson and Johnson Leader First Aid Kit. We LOVE the red, white, and blue design. This kit is marked "Made in U.S.A" and also has New Brunswick, NJ and Chicago, ILL marked on the lid. Thumb-press opener for easy access to supplies. Kit contains: • J&J Burn Ointment • Red Cross Adhesive Tape (unopened) • Red Cross Bandage packages (3 total/2 unopened) • Bottle of general antiseptic • Scissors Dimensions: 7.5Lx5Wx1.5D

name: 1940s Bicycle Pump
description: Pump it. Beautiful example of early 1940's bicycle design. Wood handle with metal body. U.S. stamped on the bottom. Perfect amount of rust and patina for it's' age. Great for display- not in working order. Black with black painted handle.

name: Model T Ignition Coil (pair)
description: 6 volt. Vintage pair of Model T ignition coils in beautifully built wooden boxes. Not sure if they still work or not, but we suggest a new pair of bookends.

name: Ornate Wall Hook
description: Layered texture. Hand-carved wooden and metal wall hook. Beautiful design. Fantastic patina. Dimensions: 5.75"Wx4.5"Lx1.5"D

name: Vintage Book Collection- Cold
description: Northern exposure. Four vintage books that simply belong together on your shelf. Color, texture, and subject matter come together perfectly. All books in great condition. Books in collection: • "The Great North Trail" Copyright, 1966 First Edition • "Raw North" Copyright, 1947 • "The World of Ice" Copyright, 1962 • "An Arctic Rodeo" Copyright, 1929

name: Industrial Art Litho #2- Original(1892)
description: Symmetry and design. Original industrial art litho print from 1892- "Types of Nails and Spikes". Original print by Sackett and Wilhelms Litho Co New York. Amazing detail and history of the nail. Great industrial design art piece with symmetry, composition, and form. Professionally matted on acid-free archival matt board with foam core backing. Excellent condition- very few marks. No rips or tears within matted area. Print Dimensions: 16"Wx20"T Matt Dimensions: 22"Wx28"T

name: Mid Century Cocktail Recipe Book
description: Best friend. This is by far one of the best mid century finds we have ever come across. Published in 1941, this rare WOODEN, metal, and leather book features a wide range of extinct and near extinct cocktails that will soon be brought back to life. Carved, mustache-clad characters on front wooden cover. Form AND function- the conversation piece at any dinner party. Cheers. Dimensions: 6"Wx9.5"L

name: Chrome + Acrylic Globe
description: Topo love. Mid Century illuminated globe with acrylic pedestal and chrome base. Fantastic vintage condition- some light scratching on acrylic and some very light surface rust and scratching on chrome. Dimensions: 36"Hx11"W • 12" diameter • Blue ocean • Manufacturer: Replogle • Made in the USA

name: Mid Century School Chair
description: Smart curves. Bent plywood and metal American-made chair to take you back to earlier times. Clean, simple lines and solid craftsmanship make this one of our favorite pieces. Nice patina on wood- some scratches and some minor light surface rust on metal, but overall in great condition. Seat height: 17"H

name: Skeleton Keys (set of three)
description: Classic romantic. Antique, rustic skeleton keys with great character. Receive a collection of three random keys- each key averages three inches in length.

name: Carabiner Barn Pulley #2
description: Clip it. Rare, vintage wood and metal pulley with carabiner-style clip. Heavy with nice detail. Heavy Patina. Dimensions: 10 1/2"Lx4"Wx41/2"D

name: Carabiner Barn Pulley #1
description: Clip it. Rare, vintage wood and metal pulley with carabiner-style clip. Heavy with nice detail. Heavy Patina. Dimensions: 10 1/2"Lx4"Wx41/2"D

name: Green Shopping Cart
description: Mother ship. Rare, old school shopping cart made in the good ol' USA. Metal, wood, and fabulous green paint come together to create the best storage device your room has ever seen. Two removable metal baskets can be used to mix up your display or taken to the store to carry your goods. Or use as a side table or lamp table. Pretty darn good condition for it's age- it dates back to the 20's/30s. Some paints a peelin', some minor surface rust here and there...casters roll smooth with some character squeaks. This things oozes with character. Oh yeah, it folds up! Dimensions: 26"Lx15"Wx38"H

name: Vintage Typewriter
description: Word machine. Stylish Smith Cornona Corsair Deluxe in duo tone and chrome. Superb condition with great detail and plastic carrying case so you can take this with you to the coffee shop. They won't mind.

name: 1920s Camp Stool
description: Camp love. Vintage camping stool from the 1920s-1930s. Clever fold-up design. Has a very beautiful, minimalistic design aesthetic. Great patina, some peeling paint, and the canvas has some perfectly placed spots. We're not exactly sure if you'd want to use this for sitting by the fire this weekend, but it would look amazing as an end table or a corner detail. You might even consider hanging it on your wall as an art piece or shelving unit- that is if you can stop using it as a footrest... Dimensions: 14"Wx16"Hx8"D

name: Vintage Book Collection- Hot
description: Killer typography. This collection will heat up any room. RED. Bold. Books in collection: • "The Cavalier" Copyright, 1901 • "The Strange Star" Copyright, 1935 • "The Penthouse Mystery" Copyright, 1941 • "If Any Man Sin" Copyright, 1915

name: Industrial Time Clock
description: Time machine. Rare 1940s Simplex time clock with bold streamline moderne/art deco design. Industrial steel gray paint job with a few chips here and there to prove it's age. Keeps great time and has a heck of a kick when you put your time card in the slot. Makes a nice healthy click every minute to remind you that you are working and not off having a picnic in a park somewhere. Heavy steel. Made in the USA.

name: Industrial Factory Cart
description: Smart cart. Our heart skipped a beat when we found this industrial factory cart. We are currently using it as a coffee table in our studio. We will be very sad to see it go. The wood has been refinished, but still retains a beautiful aged look and feel. One of the iron handles could be removed or you could turn the entire thing upside down for the most incredible bar your friends have ever seen... Dimensions: 43"Wx32"Hx25"D This baby is going to be very expensive to ship. Please contact us for an exact estimate. Local pickup in Omaha is also available- just be sure to contact us for an appointment.

name: Yellow Metal Shelf
description: Organizational master. Five shelves for all of your goodies. Vibrant yellow metal shelf with "Master" advertising on both sides. Heavy patina for rich character. Ready to hang. Dimensions: 23"Wx20"Hx9.5"D

name: Vintage Hair Dryer with Light
description: Wet dry. Art Deco. Industrial. Modern. The Tubinator demands attention. Mid century American love. This came out of a small salon in Fremont, Nebraska. Dryer functions perfectly and has summer and winter temps, as well as a light so you can look at the recent issue of Look. Very good condition for it's age- some minor surface rust here and there that adds to the character. Steel base has great deco details and some very nice patina that could be restored, but we like it the way it is. Head has a very unique tilting mechanism with art deco details. The head is somewhat adjustable, but not as much as when it was new. Cord is in great shape. This would be a fantastic addition to any hair salon, mid century home or loft space, or someone just looking for an amazing detail piece to finish their space. 25"Wx56"H

name: Giant Skeleton Keys
description: Big bones. You're in the jailhouse now...Two larger than life skeleton keys. Display with old books, maps, or just by themselves on your coffee table or counter. Or break out of jail.

name: Jet Barn Pulley
description: Zip Line. Wood and metal pulley with incredible "JET" typography. HEAVY with nice patina and character. Hang it or lay it- makes an awesome display. Dimensions: 5"Wx15"Tx5"D

name: Industrial Art Litho #1- Original(1892)
description: Web machines. Original industrial art litho print from 1892- "Printing Machines--Web". Original print by Sackett and Wilhelms Litho Co New York. Amazing detail and history of the printing press. Professionally matted on acid-free archival matt board with foam core backing. Excellent condition- very few marks. No rips or tears. Print Dimensions: 16"Wx20"T Matt Dimensions: 22"Wx28"T

name: Vintage Plumb Bobs
description: Spin it. Three (3) vintage plumb bobs. Each one a unique piece of art. Hang them from hooks. Arrange them on your coffee table. Then rearrange them. Your friends will be amazed and you will get to say "plumb-bob" on a regular basis, which is really fun. They roll. They might spin...

name: Midwest Milk Bottle
description: Midwest quality. Midwest glass milk bottle. Snip a little branch off your fern and use this as a vase to bring a little color into your work space. Or just use it as a carafe from sun up to sun down. Great "Midwest" logo and typography. Love the seal of quality. No chips or cracks. one quart. 10" tall

name: Coronado Fan
description: Smooth operator. Amazing blue fan with knight logo, great typography, and industrial aluminum blades. On/off switch on back- oscillates smoothly. Great vintage condition. Dimensions: 14"Wx17"H

name: Vintage Book Collection- Travel
description: Library Scent. Bring a little touch of the outdoors in. A nice collection of vintage books that follows a travel, tonal, and texture theme. Books in collection: • "The Islands of the Pacific" Copyright, 1895 • "Working North From Patagonia" Copyright, 1921 • "Wilderness" Copyright, 1961 • "Seven League Boots" Copyright, 1935

name: Calf Muzzle
description: Form + Function. From the farm, but this belongs on your wall as a stand alone art piece or as a small storage piece for your collection of widgets. Vintage piece with great patina. Very nice.

name: 4 Tracks Sign
description:
Hi Fidelity. Heavy metal sign with holes for hanging. Most likely from a railroad yard, but we like to think it was from some sort of industrial disco recording studio.

Dimensions: 17 1/2Wx16 3/4H

name: Toledo Candy Scale
description:
Weight watchers. Precision machinery made back east. The serial number corresponds with a candy scale, but we're not exactly sure what the city of Omaha was using this for. It could have been candy...

Form and function go hand in hand with this piece. Beautiful. Cast metal hangs out with some nice chrome, glass, and typography. Made in the USA. 1961

You can view more images on our blog:
http://www.admiraldistrict.com/?p=73

name: Antique Metal Suitcase
description:
Run away. Pack it up and hit the road. Plenty of room for all of your precious cargo. Tin suitcase with leather handle and colored stripes.

dimensions: 25"Wx13.5"Dx7"H

•tin
•leather handle
•great patina
•green and yellow stripes
•made in the USA

name: Waco Clipboard
description: Build it. Vintage clipboard with Waco Scaffolding advertising. Diagram of scaffolding in case you need to put some together on the fly. This will come in handy.

name: Civil Defense Helmet
description: Protect yourself. This helmet has seen some serious action. HEAVY. Bold graphic, intricate harness system, and curious dents. An excellent conversation piece for any room. •white helmet with circular blue, white, and red logo •adjustable harness

name: Industrial Stool with Foot Rest
description: Eye do. Super rare optometrist's examination stool with built in footrest. The perfect cure for writer's block. Steadily plant one foot on footrest and then push off aggressively in the direction of your choice. Repeat often. This rig is heavy duty and solid materials consist of steel, wood, vinyl, and rubber. Really great condition for it's age. Character? You bet! Some minor surface rust and some scratches here and there. One very minor tear on seat. Made by Brooklyn Hospital Equipment Co. in Johnstown, PA. specs and dimensions: 14"Wx10"Dx11.5"H •vintage good •solid steel construction •black vinyl seat •built in footrest •seat height adjustable from approximately 32-40" •made in the USA

name: Vintage Taxidermy Quail
description:
We came across this delightful little fellow and just knew that he would be the perfect addition to somebody’s nook or cranny. He has transitioned quite comfortably to life in our studio and has become known as “Howard”. Vintage quail mounted to wood/bark base. Beautiful condition. You can view more photos on our blog here: http://www.admiraldistrict.com/?p=7

Dimensions: 5"Wx5"Dx8"H

name: Nautical Folk Art- Horn Ship #1
description:
Crafty craftsmanship inspired by land and sea- this bull horn has been artfully transformed into an oceanic vessel. Folk art from the 1960s made from wire, metal, and bull horn. Base made of aluminum and wood. 

Dimensions: 14"Wx2.75"Dx10.75"H

name: Industrial Light Fixture
description:
This industrial fixture is brand new and in the box, but from the late 1940s to mid 1950s. It was intended to be an outside fixture, but we say bring it on inside. Mount above your sink or on any wall for a great architectural detail. Made by Steber and manufactured in the good ol' USA. Even the box is made in the US!

dimensions: 10" diameter, 13" arm

•white industrial lighting fixture
•painted silver arm
•unique mounting plate marked "Steber"
•bulb not included
•made in the USA

name: Art Deco Storage Cabinet
description:
This cabinet has 5 speeds and cruise control. It's fast and ready to roll around your loft, studio, or creative space. An ingenious blend of industrial and art deco design. Display space up top- cocktails anyone? And plenty of room for storage underneath. This unit has limitless possibilities. 

dimensions: 20"Wx15.5"Dx351/4"H

•industrial green
•solid steel construction
•metal pulls
•art deco styling
•2 storage shelves 
•2 unique drawers
•casters

name: Wooden Ammo Box
description:
Farm-fresh wooden box with bomb stencil and killer typography. Perfect for creating a little dimension in your space, bringing in a little wood, or showcasing your favorite stuffed quail. 

dimensions: 15.5"Wx14"Dx10.5"h

name: Notary Stamp
description: Once an innovative tool that saw daily use at the Leshara State Bank- now a beautiful piece of historical art that has similar characteristics to that of a pronghorn. Amazing detail. Perfect amount of patina. Still works. Font is fantastic!

name: Industrial Organizer
description: Solid design. HEAVY. This must have been used in a jet engine testing facility. Solid steel. They aren't made like this anymore. Artistic patina. At a young age of 70, it's clear to see that this beast will last forever. We LOVE it. Dimensions: 16.5"Lx10.5"Wx10"H

name: Railroad Signal
description: Choo choo. Hang it from the rafters. Bolt it to your wall. Have a friend help you put it on the top shelf...it's not THAT heavy, but it is a fine example of well-machined American railroad history. Vibrant, hefty, and fun. Electrical components have not been tested.

name: Vintage Camera Collection #2
description: Instant collector. Super eclectic grouping of cameras in this collection- dating back almost one hundred years. Chrome, leather, bakelite, and precision optics combine with beautiful typography and old school US craftsmanship to make this a truly unique grouping of photographic tools and highly sought after collectibles. Amazing as a group or as individual pieces of art in any room. Here’s what you get: • Eastman Kodak Co. No 1 Kodak Jr- 1913 • Kodak Brownie Target Six-16- 1946-1951 • Argus Seventy-Five- early 50s • Polaroid Model 80A with Wink-Light- 1957-1959 • Polaroid SX-70 Land Camera- 1972

name: Kodak Brownie Lamp
description: AD original. The perfect desktop lamp for photogs, lamp lovers, or those who just love cool things inspired by the art deco era. Two Kodak cameras along for the ride- both camera shutters still work perfectly, so the lamp is a really fun distraction to have on your desk! The base camera is a 1924 Kodak Brownie 2a and the top camera is a 1941ish Kodak Brownie Target Six-16 with geometric deco design. All new electrical components. Hand made in the USA. • 30 watt radio filament bub • nickel plated turn key • 9' of cloth covered cord • 1920s style plug

name: Shoe Form Lamp #1
description: AD original. The perfect combination of vintage wood and chrome. The 1962 era shoe form balances perfectly in any room. Bright enough for a task light or just adding a nice touch of ambiance. All new electrical components. • 60 watt Edison bulb • about 9' of cloth covered cord • 1920s style vintage plug

name: Sprinkler Lamp
description: AD original. Vintage mid century sprinkler base that walks the line between industrial and art deco. This little fella will compliment any table or shelf. All new electrical components. • 30 watt radio filament bulb • about 9' of cloth covered cord • 1920's style plug • nickel-plated turnkey

name: Vintage Book Lamp- Insects
description: AD original. Another Department of Agriculture classic from the Mid Century. This 1952 vintage book lamp, entitled "Insects", has bold graphics and beautiful retro design and will serve you well as a task light for reading another book about insects or as a nice source of ambiance on any shelf. We believe in details. This vintage book lamp comes with a perfectly placed turn knob switch, about 9’ of vintage looking cloth covered cord, a 1920’s style plug, and a 60 watt Edison style bulb. All new electrical components.

name: Vintage Book Lamp- Animal Diseases
description: AD original. The Yearbook of Agriculture 1956. The title says it all. Iconic graphics, mid century fonts, and clever placement of the toggle switch make sure this book will be the main conversation piece in any room. We believe in details. This vintage book lamp comes with a perfectly placed toggle switch, about 9’ of vintage looking cloth covered cord, a 1920’s style plug, and a 60 watt Edison style bulb. All new electrical components.

name: Vintage Book Lamp- Admiral of the Ocean Sea
description: AD original. This up-cycled vintage book lamp is the conversation piece of any room. This lamp features the vintage hardcover book, "Admiral of the Ocean Sea". Beautiful, vintage crimson cover that dates back to 1942 and has the perfect amount of wear. We believe in details. This vintage book lamp comes with a perfectly placed turn knob switch, about 9’ of vintage looking cloth covered cord, a 1920’s style plug, and a 60 watt Edison style bulb. All new electrical components.

name: Vintage Book Lamp- The Virginian
description: AD original. This up-cycled vintage book lamp is the conversation piece in any room. This lamp features the vintage hardcover book, “The Virginian”. This book has a sublime linen-like cover featuring a gold and maroon graphic of a cowboy and his horse. We believe in details. This vintage book lamp comes with a perfectly placed turn knob switch, about 9’ of vintage looking cloth covered cord, a 1920’s style plug, and a 60 watt Edison style bulb. All new electrical components.

name: Vintage Book Lamp- Popular Science
description: AD original. This upcycled vintage book lamp is the conversation piece in any room. This lamp features two 1959 editions of “The Book of Popular Science” stacked together for good measure. These books have great Mid Century typography and a nice woven texture. The cover illustration is a cutaway shell of the chambered nautilus- the work of Edward Weston. We believe in details. This vintage book lamp comes with a perfectly placed turn knob switch, about 9’ of vintage looking cloth covered cord, a 1920’s style plug, and a 30 watt Edison style bulb. All new electrical components.
